article_title: Delos Cosgrove Takes His Name Out of Contention for Top VA Job
article_text:
Delos "Toby" Cosgrove, chief executive of the Cleveland Clinic, withdrew his name from consideration to be the next secretary of the Department of Veterans Affairs.

Dr. Cosgrove, 73, had been asked by President Barack Obama to consider leading the department which is under intense political fire stemming from problems including delays in patient care and mismanagement. Eric Shinseki, the former head of the agency, resigned...
